    <h1>One-Pan White Cheddar Mac and Cheese</h1>
    <img src="https://www.allrecipes.com/thmb/GNjcqH8gWxfaQv8uuFeEH6mnm38=/2250x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():gifv()/5925391-3978823c3d6f4b0e80a4fb5ff2033db6.jpg" >
    <strong><h3>One-Pan White Cheddar Mac and Cheese</h3></strong>
    <p>If you can make boxed macaroni and cheese, you can make this one-pan, scratch-made mac and cheese! The bacon, chives, and.</p>
    <p>crispy bread crumb topping add some great extra flavor and texture.</p>
    <h2>Ingredients</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>16 ounces uncooked elbow macaroni</li>
      <li>2 ½ cups milk</li>
      <li>2 cups water</li>
      <li>1 teaspoon garlic salt</li>
      <li>½ teaspoon salt</li>
      <li>¼ cup margarine</li>
      <li>¼ teaspoon ground black pepper</li>
      <li>1 ½ cups shredded white Cheddar cheese/li>
      <li>1tablespoon dried parsley</li>
      <li>½ cup shredded Parmesan cheese, divided</li>
      <li>¼ cup panko bread crumbs</li>
      <li>¼ cup real bacon bits</li>
      <li>1 tablespoon snipped chives</li>
      <h2>Steps</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>Combine macroni, milk,water, garlic salt, and salt in a Dutch oven on a</p>
        <p>sotovetop over medium-high heat. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Reduce</p>
        <p>heat to a simmer and cook, stirring frequently so noodles don't stick to the pan,</p>
        <p>until noodles are soft and most of the liquid has been absorbed, 7 to 10 minutes</p>
      </li>
      <li><p>Remove pot from and stir in margarine and pepper until melted. Stir in</p>
        <p>Cheddar cheese and 1/4 cup of the Parmesan chesse until melted</p>
        <li>
          <p>Set an oven rack about 6 inches from the heat souce and preheat the oven's broiler</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>TOp pasta with bread crumbs, remaining 1/4 cup of Parmesan cheese, and</p>
          <p>bacon bits</p>
          <li>
            <p>Place Dutcg oven under the broiler until topping is lighttly browned and crispy, 1 </p>
            <p>to 3 minutes. Top with chives and serve immediately</p>
          </li>
        </li>
      </li>
    </ol>
    </ul>
  </body>
